The paper deals with the analysis of diversity in multihop relay channels with multi-antenna sources and destinations. This topic falls under the field of information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also discusses cooperative decode-and-forward schemes, which are commonly used in communication systems (cs.COMM). Additionally, the paper proposes a flip-and-forward scheme, which involves space-time relay processing and falls under the category of multiple-input multiple-output (MIMO) systems (cs.MM). Finally, the paper discusses coding schemes, which are relevant to systems and control (cs.SY).
